Sentencas: The Ruddlesden-Popper phase, (Nd0.9La0.1)(2)(Ni0.74Cu0.21Al0.05)O4+delta (NLNCA), has been investigated as an alternative cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Novel cobalt-free cathode material (Nd0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Al0.05)O4+δ for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its electrical conductivity is 51-60 S cm(-1) over the temperature range of 650-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Novel cobalt-free cathode material (Nd0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Al0.05)O4+δ for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal-expansion coefficient (TEC) value of NLNCA is 13.2 x 10(-6) K-1.
Titulo: Novel cobalt-free cathode material (Nd0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Al0.05)O4+δ for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the NLNCA cathode measured on a Sm0 2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte reaches a relatively low value of 0.048 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. A maximum power density of 521 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 800 degrees C for single-cell with thickness of similar to 300 mu m SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Novel cobalt-free cathode material (Nd0.9La0.1)2(Ni0.74Cu0.21Al0.05)O4+δ for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
